{
  "texts": [
    "Not all customization is harmful.",
    "It is essential to differentiate between using algorithmic customization approaches (e.g., unsupervised learning, latent pattern mining, anomaly detection, dimensionality reduction, etc.)",
    "to discover verifiable knowledge versus to adapt the delivery of knowledge to ensure palatability and user acceptance.",
    "This distinction (illustrated in Fig. 1) can help evaluate the rationale behind customization and align it with application goals.",
    "Consider an AI-powered radiology tool that identifies relevant areas of a medical image and tailors outputs in line with a radiologist's preferences and past interactions with the system."
  ]
}